[SN]TITLE[SN]
Trapped in unusual places: Your stories

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A portable toilet with a woman inside was accidentally carried across a festival site by a forklift truck. The woman had gone to use the toilet ahead of the opening of the Newlyn Fish Festival in Cornwall.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
You have been sharing your stories of the worst places that you have been trapped. Here are a selection of of them.
@Vivienne17 tweets about getting stuck in a loo during a train journey.
@Dennis99 was rescued by the fire brigade after he got stuck.
In Northamptonshire, a cow managed to get its head stuck through a plastic garden chair.  The cow managed to extricate itself from the chair without assistance.
Who can forget David Willis, who was accidentally locked in a Waterstones bookshop.  We wonder what happened to him?
And finally, who can forget the Mayor of London Boris Johnson being trapped on a zip wire after it became stuck during an Olympic event in 2012?
